cdmipSmtpServerIpAddress.description: IP address of the SMTP server on your local LAN.

cdmipSmtpDestinationName.name: cdmipSmtpDestinationName
cdmipSmtpDestinationName.description: SMTP Destination Email User Name (i.e. cdmipsupport)

cdmipSnmpTrapDestinationIpAddress.name: cdmipSnmpTrapDestinationIpAddress
cdmipSnmpTrapDestinationIpAddress.description: SNMP Trap Destination #1: The primary IP Address to which trap will be sent.

cdmipSnmpTrapCommunity.name: cdmipSnmpTrapCommunity
cdmipSnmpTrapCommunity.description: The trap community string to be used for SNMP trap messages.

cdmipSnmpTrapVersion.name: cdmipSnmpTrapVersion
cdmipSnmpTrapVersion.description: The SNMP Trap Version: Use V1 for SNMP Version 1 Traps. Use V2 for SNMP Version 2 Notifications.

cdmipSnmpAuthenticationFailureCommunity.name: cdmipSnmpAuthenticationFailureCommunity
cdmipSnmpAuthenticationFailureCommunity.description: NOTE: Used ONLY in the Authentification Failure Trap (No access). The community string which was invalid for a SET or GET SNMP message.

cdmipSnmpAuthenticationFailureAddress.name: cdmipSnmpAuthenticationFailureAddress
cdmipSnmpAuthenticationFailureAddress.description: NOTE: Used ONLY in the Authentification Failure Trap (No access). IP Address which sent an SNMP message with an invalid SET or GET community string.

cdmipSnmpTrapDestinationIpAddress2.name: cdmipSnmpTrapDestinationIpAddress2
cdmipSnmpTrapDestinationIpAddress2.description: SNMP Trap Destination #2: The secondary IP Address to which traps will be sent.

cdmipWorkingMode.name: cdmipWorkingMode
cdmipWorkingMode.description: Configure the IP Card's working mode. The CDM-IP can operate in any of these modes. 1. Router - Small Network Mode: The system functions as router and uses the route table to determine how to forward packets in a small network HDLC address mode. The HDLC packet uses a 1 byte HDLC address. The valid values are from 1 to 254 (0x1 - 0xFE). 2. Router - Large Network Mode: The system functions as router and uses the route table to determine how to forward packets in a large network HDLC address mode. The HDLC packet uses a 2- byte HDLC address. The valid values are from 1 to 32766 (0x1 - 0x7FFE). 3. Router - Point to Point - The system functions as router and uses the route table to determine how to forward packets in a point-to-point HDLC address mode. The HDLC packet does not use a HDLC address. 4. Router - Vipersat Mode - The system functions in Vipersat mode. 5. EasyConnect mode - The system forwards all packets it receives. The HDLC packet does not use a HDLC address. *** IMPORTANT NOTE *** Changing Working mode requires the system to reboot. System configuration is saved before rebooting. Please make sure you are setting the correct value.

cdmipEasyconnectMulticastOption.name: cdmipEasyconnectMulticastOption
cdmipEasyconnectMulticastOption.description: Enable/Disable the Easyconnect multicast option. Enabling this option allows the modem working in EasyConnect operation to pass multicast traffic.

cdmipHdrcompRefreshRateUdpRtp1.name: cdmipHdrcompRefreshRateUdpRtp1
cdmipHdrcompRefreshRateUdpRtp1.description: Header compression Refresh Rate for UDP/RTP1. Valid range is 1 - 600 packets per full IP/UDP/RTP Header.

cdmipHdrcompRefreshRateUdp.name: cdmipHdrcompRefreshRateUdp
cdmipHdrcompRefreshRateUdp.description: Header Compression Refresh Rate for UDP. Valid range is 1 - 600 packets per full IP/UDP Header.

cdmipHdrcompRefreshRateAllOther.name: cdmipHdrcompRefreshRateAllOther
cdmipHdrcompRefreshRateAllOther.description: Header Compression Refresh Rate for all other protocols. Valid range is 1 - 600 packet per full IP Header.

cdmipPayloadCompRefreshRate.name: cdmipPayloadCompRefreshRate
cdmipPayloadCompRefreshRate.description: Refresh rate for Payload Compression in packets. Valid range is 1 = 600 packets before a refresh ofthe payload compression algorithm is done.

cdmipEthernetMacAddress.name: cdmipEthernetMacAddress
cdmipEthernetMacAddress.description: The MAC address for the Ethernet interface.

cdmipEthernetSpeed.name: cdmipEthernetSpeed
cdmipEthernetSpeed.description: The speed and mode of the Ehternet interface: The valid settings are: 1. Automatic. 2. 10 Mbps - Half Duplex. 3. 100 Mpbs - Half Duplex. 4. 10 Mbps - Full Duplex. 5. 100 Mbps - Full Duplex.

cdmipEthernetIpAddress.name: cdmipEthernetIpAddress
cdmipEthernetIpAddress.description: The IP address for the Ethernet interface.

cdmipEthernetSubnetPrefixLen.name: cdmipEthernetSubnetPrefixLen
cdmipEthernetSubnetPrefixLen.description: The subnet mask prefix length for the Ethernet interface.

cdmipSatelliteHdlcAddress1.name: cdmipSatelliteHdlcAddress1
cdmipSatelliteHdlcAddress1.description: HDLC Channel Address #1 filtered by the HSR Valid values of HDLC address depends on the Network mode. In Small Network Mode - Frame will have 1 Byte of HDLC addr. valid values are 1 - 254. (0x1 - 0xFE) In Large Network Mode - Frame will have 2 Bytes of HDLC address. valid values are 1 - 32766 (0x1 - 0x7FFE) In Point-to-Point Mode - HDLC addresses are NOT-USED. An HDLC Address of '0(Zero)' is interpretted as NOT-DEFINED or NOT-USED An HDLC address cannot have 0x00 or 0xFF in least Significant Byte. i.e., 0x400 or 0x6ff or 0x11ff are NOT valid HDLC addresses. User is NOT allowed to configure HDLC address while system is operating in EASY CONNECT MODE. To Invalidate/Delete HDLC Address, set the MIB member 'cdmipSatelliteHdlcAddressDelete' to the HDLC address number. HDLC Address number range from 1...4

cdmipSatelliteHdlcAddress2.name: cdmipSatelliteHdlcAddress2
cdmipSatelliteHdlcAddress2.description: HDLC Channel Address #2 filtered by the HSR Valid values of HDLC address depends on the Network mode. In Small Network Mode - Frame will have 1 Byte of HDLC addr. valid values are 1 - 254. (0x1 - 0xFE) In Large Network Mode - Frame will have 2 Bytes of HDLC address. valid values are 1 - 32766 (0x1 - 0x7FFE) In Point-to-Point Mode - HDLC addresses are NOT-USED. An HDLC Address of '0(Zero)' is interpretted as NOT-DEFINED or NOT-USED An HDLC address cannot have 0x00 or 0xFF in least Significant Byte. i.e., 0x400 or 0x6ff or 0x11ff are NOT valid HDLC addresses. User is NOT allowed to configure HDLC address while system is operating in EASY CONNECT MODE. To Invalidate/Delete HDLC Address, set the MIB member 'cdmipSatelliteHdlcAddressDelete' to the HDLC address number. HDLC Address number range from 1...4

cdmipSatelliteHdlcAddress3.name: cdmipSatelliteHdlcAddress3
cdmipSatelliteHdlcAddress3.description: HDLC Channel Address #3 filtered by the HSR Valid values of HDLC address depends on the Network mode. In Small Network Mode - Frame will have 1 Byte of HDLC addr. valid values are 1 - 254. (0x1 - 0xFE) In Large Network Mode - Frame will have 2 Bytes of HDLC address. valid values are 1 - 32766 (0x1 - 0x7FFE) In Point-to-Point Mode - HDLC addresses are NOT-USED. An HDLC Address of '0(Zero)' is interpretted as NOT-DEFINED or NOT-USED An HDLC address cannot have 0x00 or 0xFF in least Significant Byte. i.e., 0x400 or 0x6ff or 0x11ff are NOT valid HDLC addresses. User is NOT allowed to configure HDLC address while system is operating in EASY CONNECT MODE. To Invalidate/Delete HDLC Address, set the MIB member 'cdmipSatelliteHdlcAddressDelete' to the HDLC address number. HDLC Address number range from 1...4

cdmipSatelliteHdlcAddress4.name: cdmipSatelliteHdlcAddress4
cdmipSatelliteHdlcAddress4.description: HDLC Channel Address #4 filtered by the HSR Valid values of HDLC address depends on the Network mode. In Small Network Mode - Frame will have 1 Byte of HDLC addr. valid values are 1 - 254. (0x1 - 0xFE) In Large Network Mode - Frame will have 2 Bytes of HDLC address. valid values are 1 - 32766 (0x1 - 0x7FFE) In Point-to-Point Mode - HDLC addresses are NOT-USED. An HDLC Address of '0(Zero)' is interpretted as NOT-DEFINED or NOT-USED An HDLC address cannot have 0x00 or 0xFF in least Significant Byte. i.e., 0x400 or 0x6ff or 0x11ff are NOT valid HDLC addresses. User is NOT allowed to configure HDLC address while system is operating in EASY CONNECT MODE. To Invalidate/Delete HDLC Address, set the MIB member 'cdmipSatelliteHdlcAddressDelete' to the HDLC address number. HDLC Address number range from 1...4

cdmipSatelliteHdlcAddressDelete.name: cdmipSatelliteHdlcAddressDelete
cdmipSatelliteHdlcAddressDelete.description: Used to delete a specified HDLC Address. Setting this entry to value 1...4 deletes/invalidates the corresponding HDLC Address. 1. for HDLCAddress #1 2. for HDLCAddress #2 3. for HDLCAddress #3 4. for HDLCAddress #4 When a HDLC Address is deleted/invalidated, it is displayed as '0' (NOT-DEFINED or NOT-USED) on SNMP Gets.

cdmipSatelliteHdlcAddressModeConfig.name: cdmipSatelliteHdlcAddressModeConfig
cdmipSatelliteHdlcAddressModeConfig.description: The size of HDLC address used for frames sent over the satellite interface can range from 0 - 2 bytes. This range allows the system to operate in one of these modes: 1. Small Network Mode - The frame will have 1 byte of HDLC address. Valid values are 1 - 254. (0x1 - 0xFE). 2. Large Network Mode - The frame will have 2 bytes of HDLC address. Valid values are 1 - 32767 (0x1 - 0x7FFE). 3. Point-to-Point Mode - The frame does not use any HDLC address. 4. Vipersat Mode - The frame does not use any HDLC address.

cdmipIpRouteIndex.name: cdmipIpRouteIndex
cdmipIpRouteIndex.description: The index for the route table.

cdmipIpRouteName.name: cdmipIpRouteName
cdmipIpRouteName.description: The name for the route. The route name must be unique.

cdmipIpRouteDestAddress.name: cdmipIpRouteDestAddress
cdmipIpRouteDestAddress.description: The destination IP address for the route. ***Note***: Do not add multicast routes for Vipersat Multicast addresses.

cdmipIpRouteDestMaskLen.name: cdmipIpRouteDestMaskLen
cdmipIpRouteDestMaskLen.description: The number of bits in the subnet mask for the destination IP address for the route.

cdmipIpRouteNextHopAddress.name: cdmipIpRouteNextHopAddress
cdmipIpRouteNextHopAddress.description: The Next Hop IP Address is valid only for routes destined to the Ethernet interface. This IP address must be a locally attached router. Set 'cdmipIpRouteState' to 'toEthernet' state before setting 'cdmipIpRouteNextHopAddress'.

cdmipIpRouteMulticastOptions.name: cdmipIpRouteMulticastOptions
cdmipIpRouteMulticastOptions.description: Configures how router should handle multicast traffic. Valid options are: 1. Do not forward any multicast traffic (drop all). 2. Forward multicast traffic from Ethernet to Satellite only. 3. Forward multicast traffic from Satellite to Ethernet only. 4. Forward multicast traffic in both directions.

cdmipIpRouteState.name: cdmipIpRouteState
cdmipIpRouteState.description: The route state specifies the route's destination. The valid values are: 1. To Ethernet (route goes to Ethernet interface). 2. To Satellite (route goes to Satellite interface).

cdmipIpRouteHdlcAddress.name: cdmipIpRouteHdlcAddress
cdmipIpRouteHdlcAddress.description: The HDLC Address is valid only for routes destined to the Satellite interface. This can also be viewed as the 'next-hop' identifier for the route destined to satellite. The valid range of HDLC Address depends on Network mode. 1. Small Network mode - 1 - 254 (0x01 - 0xFE) 2. Large Network Mode - 1 - 32766 (0x01 - 0x7FFE) An HDLC Address cannot have 0x00 or 0xFF in Least Significant Byte (LSB). Set 'cdmipIpRouteState' to 'toSatellite' state before setting 'cdmipIpRouteHdlcAddress'.

cdmipIpRouteHdrComp.name: cdmipIpRouteHdrComp
cdmipIpRouteHdrComp.description: Enable or disable IP header compression on this route. To Set this parameter, you need to have Header Compression Feature available on your modem. It may return 'commit_failed' if feature is not available on modem.

cdmipIpRoutePayloadComp.name: cdmipIpRoutePayloadComp
cdmipIpRoutePayloadComp.description: Enable or disable payload compression on this route. To set this parameter, you need to have Datagram/Payload Compression feature available on your modem. It may return 'commit_failed' if feature is not available on modem.

cdmipIpRoute3xDes.name: cdmipIpRoute3xDes
cdmipIpRoute3xDes.description: Enable or disable 3xDES [Triple DES Encryption] on this route. It may return 'commit_failed' if 3xDES feature is not available on modem.

cdmipIpRouteDesKey.name: cdmipIpRouteDesKey
cdmipIpRouteDesKey.description: Pick which DES key to use for this route. The system supports 8 3xDES (Triple DES - 24 Byte Length) keys. This specifies the 3xDES key to be used for this flow. 1 - 8 for Key1 to Key8 9 - Randomly pick one of the 8 keys. 10 - Clear

cdmipIpRouteRowStatus.name: cdmipIpRouteRowStatus
cdmipIpRouteRowStatus.description: In SMIv2 tables, the RowStatus textual convention is used to manage the creation and deletion of conceptual rows. This column has six defined values. active(1) - which indicates that the conceptual row with all column is available for use by the managed device notInService(2) - this row state is not yet supported notReady(3) - this row state is not yet supported createAndGo(4) - which is supplied by a manager wishing to create a new instance of a conceptual row and to have its status automatically set to active, making it available for use by the managed device. createAndWait(5) - this row create is not yet supported destroy(6) - which is supplied by a manager wishing to delete all of the instances associated with an existing conceptual row.

cdmipIgmpIndex.name: cdmipIgmpIndex
cdmipIgmpIndex.description: The index for the IGMP table.

cdmipIgmpTTL.name: cdmipIgmpTTL
cdmipIgmpTTL.description: The IGMP Time to live (TTL) for the multicast group.

cdmipIgmpClientState.name: cdmipIgmpClientState
cdmipIgmpClientState.description: The current state of the multicast group. Possible states are: 1. Idle. 2. Active. 3. Closing.

cdmipIgmpSrc.name: cdmipIgmpSrc
cdmipIgmpSrc.description: Show which interface the multicast group is coming from. Possible values are: 1. Other - from the Ethernet interface. 2. Sat - from the Satellite interface.

cdmipIgmpGroupIpAddress.name: cdmipIgmpGroupIpAddress
cdmipIgmpGroupIpAddress.description: The multicast address for the IGMP group.

cdmipIgmpEnable.name: cdmipIgmpEnable
cdmipIgmpEnable.description: Enable or disable IGMP. 1. IGMP is enabled. 2. IGMP is disabled.

cdmipIgmpQueryPeriod.name: cdmipIgmpQueryPeriod
cdmipIgmpQueryPeriod.description: Modem as IGMP Server: IGMP query period in seconds.

cdmipIgmpMaxRespTime.name: cdmipIgmpMaxRespTime
cdmipIgmpMaxRespTime.description: Modem as Sever: IGMP max. response time in seconds.

cdmipIgmpMaxMissBeforeDrop.name: cdmipIgmpMaxMissBeforeDrop
cdmipIgmpMaxMissBeforeDrop.description: Modem as Server: Number of missed responses before leaving an IGMP group.

cdmipIgmpRecognizeQueries.name: cdmipIgmpRecognizeQueries
cdmipIgmpRecognizeQueries.description: Modem as Client: Recognize IGMP Queries

cdmipIgmpVersionUnsolicitedReports.name: cdmipIgmpVersionUnsolicitedReports
cdmipIgmpVersionUnsolicitedReports.description: Modem as Client: IGMP Version used for Unsolicited Reports. Possible values are: 1. Version 1. 2. Version 2.

cdmipIgmpForceAlertOption.name: cdmipIgmpForceAlertOption
cdmipIgmpForceAlertOption.description: Modem as Client: Router Alert Option for V1 report.

cdmipIgmpUnsolicitedReportInterval.name: cdmipIgmpUnsolicitedReportInterval
cdmipIgmpUnsolicitedReportInterval.description: Modem as Client: Unsolicited Report Interval in seconds.

cdmipDhcpServerIpAddress.name: cdmipDhcpServerIpAddress
cdmipDhcpServerIpAddress.description: The IP address of the DHCP Server.

cdmipCurrentRedundantState.name: cdmipCurrentRedundantState
cdmipCurrentRedundantState.description: The redundancy state of the modem. 1. OnLine - actively passing IP traffic. 0. OffLine - in standby mode; no IP traffic.

cdmipLocalUnitManagementIpAddress.name: cdmipLocalUnitManagementIpAddress
cdmipLocalUnitManagementIpAddress.description: The IP Address for management of the IP parameters (READ ONLY). *** NOTE: This address is the same as the Ethernet IP address. ***

cdmipRedundantUnitManagementIpAddress.name: cdmipRedundantUnitManagementIpAddress
cdmipRedundantUnitManagementIpAddress.description: The IP Address of the redundant unit (READ ONLY). *** NOTE: This address is the same as other unit's Ethernet IP address. ***

cdmipRedundantTrafficIpAddress.name: cdmipRedundantTrafficIpAddress
cdmipRedundantTrafficIpAddress.description: The IP address for traffic passing through the redundant pair of modem. This address is only active in the ONLINE modem. *** NOTE: The traffic IP can only be set on the ONLINE unit. ***

cdmipRedundantTrafficSubnetMaskLen.name: cdmipRedundantTrafficSubnetMaskLen
cdmipRedundantTrafficSubnetMaskLen.description: The subnet mask prefix length for the traffic IP address. *** NOTE: The traffic IP subnet mask can only be set on the ONLINE unit. ***

cdmipForceUnitOffline.name: cdmipForceUnitOffline
cdmipForceUnitOffline.description: The allows the user to force a modem into standby mode. When a 'force' is executed the ONLINE unit goes to standby mode. Also, the OFFLINE unit now becomes active. *** NOTE: A 'force' can only be executed on the ONLINE unit. ***

cdmipAppVersion.name: cdmipAppVersion
cdmipAppVersion.description: Displays the version information for the application image and FPGA images.

cdmipSaveConfiguration.name: cdmipSaveConfiguration
cdmipSaveConfiguration.description: Setting this value to '1' will save the PARAM permanent storage. Only value: 1. Save - save the PARAM to permanent storage.

cdmipReset.name: cdmipReset
cdmipReset.description: Setting this value to '1' will reboot the IP card. Only value: 1. Rest - reboot the IP card.

cdmipRestoreFactoryDefaults.name: cdmipRestoreFactoryDefaults
cdmipRestoreFactoryDefaults.description: Setting this value to '1' will restore factory defaults to the system. Only value: 1. Restore - restore factory defaults. *** NOTE: Restoring factory defaults will erase PARAM in permanent storage. Make sure, before setting this to True. ***

cdmipLoadParamsFromStorage.name: cdmipLoadParamsFromStorage
cdmipLoadParamsFromStorage.description: Setting the value to '1' will load the PARAM from the permanent storage. Only value: 1. Load - load PARAM from permanent storage.

cdmipIPModuleBootFrom.name: cdmipIPModuleBootFrom
cdmipIPModuleBootFrom.description: Setting this parameter lets the IP Module to boot from a specified image. 0. Latest - boots with the image that has the latest timestamp (date and time). 1. Image 1 - boots with the image stored in Image 1. 2. Image 2 - boots with the image stored in Image 2.

cdmipUpgradeTo.name: cdmipUpgradeTo
cdmipUpgradeTo.description: Setting this parameter specifies Image to overwrite with the new upgraded image. 0. Oldest - Saves the new upgrade image over the image that has the oldest timestamp (date and time). 1. Image1 - Saves the new upgrade image into Image #1. 2. Image2 - Saves the new upgrade image into Image #2. *** NOTE: This parameter must be set before performing an upgrade. ***

cdmipParamConfig.name: cdmipParamConfig
cdmipParamConfig.description: Setting this parameter tells how the IP card will get its configuration data when booting up: Configuration data can be loaded from the following locations: 1. Factory Defaultls - load data from factory defaults. 2. PARAM File - load data from PARAM in permanent storage.

cdmipBootImageInfo.name: cdmipBootImageInfo
cdmipBootImageInfo.description: Displays version information for bootrom image.

cdmipAppImage1Info.name: cdmipAppImage1Info
cdmipAppImage1Info.description: Displays version information for application image in slot #1.

cdmipAppImage2Info.name: cdmipAppImage2Info
cdmipAppImage2Info.description: Displays version information for application image in slot #2.

cdmipFramerVersion.name: cdmipFramerVersion
cdmipFramerVersion.description: Displays version information for framer installed in the IP card.

cdmipBaseModemBootFrom.name: cdmipBaseModemBootFrom
cdmipBaseModemBootFrom.description: Setting this parameter lets the Base Modem boot from a specified image. 0. Latest - boots with the Base Modem image that has the latest timestamp (date and time). 1. Image 1 - boots with the Base Modem image stored in Image 1. 2. Image 2 - boots with the Base Modem image stored in Image 2.

cdmipEtherTransmitGoodFrames.name: cdmipEtherTransmitGoodFrames
cdmipEtherTransmitGoodFrames.description: The number of transmitted good frames from the Ethernet interface.

cdmipEtherTransmitMaxCollisionCount.name: cdmipEtherTransmitMaxCollisionCount
cdmipEtherTransmitMaxCollisionCount.description: The number of frames that were NOT transmitted because they encountered maximum configured collisions. This counter should only increment when network is heavily saturated with traffic.

cdmipEtherTransmitLateCollisionCount.name: cdmipEtherTransmitLateCollisionCount
cdmipEtherTransmitLateCollisionCount.description: The number of frames that were NOT transmitted because they encountered a collision outside the normal collision window.

cdmipEtherTransmitDMAUnderrunCount.name: cdmipEtherTransmitDMAUnderrunCount
cdmipEtherTransmitDMAUnderrunCount.description: The number of frames that were either NOT transmitted OR retransmitted due to transmit DMA underrun. Underruns occur due to lack of PCI bandwidth resulting in the internal transmit FIFO running dry during the transmission of a frame.

cdmipEtherTransmitLostCarrierSenseCount.name: cdmipEtherTransmitLostCarrierSenseCount
cdmipEtherTransmitLostCarrierSenseCount.description: The number of frames transmitted by the device despite the fact that it detected the de-assertion of Transmit Lost Carrier Sense (CRS) during the transmission.

cdmipEtherTransmitDeferredCount.name: cdmipEtherTransmitDeferredCount
cdmipEtherTransmitDeferredCount.description: The number of frames deferred before transmission due to activity on the link.

cdmipEtherTransmitSingleCollisionCount.name: cdmipEtherTransmitSingleCollisionCount
cdmipEtherTransmitSingleCollisionCount.description: The number of transmitted frames that encountered only one collision.

cdmipEtherTransmitMultipleCollisionCount.name: cdmipEtherTransmitMultipleCollisionCount
cdmipEtherTransmitMultipleCollisionCount.description: The number of transmitted frames that encountered more than one collision.

cdmipEtherTransmitTotalCollisionCount.name: cdmipEtherTransmitTotalCollisionCount
cdmipEtherTransmitTotalCollisionCount.description: This counter contains the total number of collisions that were encountered while attempting to transmit. This count includes late collisions and collisions from frames that encountered maximum collisions.

cdmipEtherReceiveGoodFrames.name: cdmipEtherReceiveGoodFrames
cdmipEtherReceiveGoodFrames.description: The number of frames properly received from the link. It is updated only after actual reception from the link is completed and all data bytes are stored in memory.

cdmipEtherReceiveCRCErrorFrameCount.name: cdmipEtherReceiveCRCErrorFrameCount
cdmipEtherReceiveCRCErrorFrameCount.description: The number of aligned frames discarded due to a CRC error.

cdmipEtherReceiveAllignErrorCount.name: cdmipEtherReceiveAllignErrorCount
cdmipEtherReceiveAllignErrorCount.description: The number of frames that are both misaligned [in other words, CRS de-asserts on a non-octet boundary] and contain a CRC error.

cdmipEtherReceiveResourceErrorCount.name: cdmipEtherReceiveResourceErrorCount
cdmipEtherReceiveResourceErrorCount.description: The number of good frames discarded to unavailable resources.

cdmipEtherReceiveFifoOverrunErrorCount.name: cdmipEtherReceiveFifoOverrunErrorCount
cdmipEtherReceiveFifoOverrunErrorCount.description: The number of frames known to be lost because the internal receive FIFO overflowed [also known as receive overrun]. This can occur if the device is unable to get necessary PCI bandwidth. If the overflow condition persists for more than one frame, the frames that follow the first can also be lost. A frame that was counted as an overrun will not be counted in other error counters, like short frames, misaligned, or CRC error.

cdmipEtherReceiveCollisionDetectErrorCou.name: cdmipEtherReceiveCollisionDetectErrorCount
cdmipEtherReceiveCollisionDetectErrorCou.description: The number of frames that encountered a collision during reception. This counter is always zero on the 82559 Ethernet chip.

cdmipEtherReceiveShortFrameCount.name: cdmipEtherReceiveShortFrameCount
cdmipEtherReceiveShortFrameCount.description: The number of received frames that are shorter than the minimum frame length.

cdmipEtherTransmitFlowControlPauseFrames.name: cdmipEtherTransmitFlowControlPauseFrames
cdmipEtherTransmitFlowControlPauseFrames.description: The number of flow control frames transmitted by the device. This count includes both the XOFF and XON frames transmitted by the device.

cdmipEtherReceiveFlowControlPauseFrames.name: cdmipEtherReceiveFlowControlPauseFrames
cdmipEtherReceiveFlowControlPauseFrames.description: The number of flow control frames received by the device. This count includes both XOFF and XON frames received.

cdmipEtherResetCounters.name: cdmipEtherResetCounters
cdmipEtherResetCounters.description: Setting this parameter to '1' will reset all Ethernet transmit and receive counters.

cdmipTotalIpPacketsFromSatellite.name: cdmipTotalIpPacketsFromSatellite
cdmipTotalIpPacketsFromSatellite.description: The total number of IP packets received from the Satellite interface.

cdmipTotalIpPacketsRoutedToSatellite.name: cdmipTotalIpPacketsRoutedToSatellite
cdmipTotalIpPacketsRoutedToSatellite.description: The total number of IP packets sent to the Satellite interface.

cdmipTotalIpPacketsFromEthernet.name: cdmipTotalIpPacketsFromEthernet
cdmipTotalIpPacketsFromEthernet.description: The total number of IP packets received from the Ethernet interface.

cdmipTotalIpPacketsRoutedToEthernet.name: cdmipTotalIpPacketsRoutedToEthernet
cdmipTotalIpPacketsRoutedToEthernet.description: The total number of IP packets sent to the Ethernet interface.

cdmipIgmpPacketsReceived.name: cdmipIgmpPacketsReceived
cdmipIgmpPacketsReceived.description: The total number of multicast IGMP packets received from any interface.

cdmipIpOptionPacketsReceived.name: cdmipIpOptionPacketsReceived
cdmipIpOptionPacketsReceived.description: The total number of packets received with IP options in the header.

cdmipDroppedPacketsTotal.name: cdmipDroppedPacketsTotal
cdmipDroppedPacketsTotal.description: The total number of packets dropped for any reason.

cdmipDroppedPacketsTTLExpired.name: cdmipDroppedPacketsTTLExpired
cdmipDroppedPacketsTTLExpired.description: The total number of packets dropped because TTL (time to live) expired.

cdmipDroppedPacketsBadIpHeader.name: cdmipDroppedPacketsBadIpHeader
cdmipDroppedPacketsBadIpHeader.description: The total number of packets dropped because of a bad IP header checksum.

cdmipDroppedPacketsNoRoute.name: cdmipDroppedPacketsNoRoute
cdmipDroppedPacketsNoRoute.description: The total number of packets dropped because of no route.

cdmipDroppedPacketsMulticast.name: cdmipDroppedPacketsMulticast
cdmipDroppedPacketsMulticast.description: The number of multicast packets dropped because of 'Satellite to Ethernet Option' is disabled.

cdmipDroppedPacketsFiltered.name: cdmipDroppedPacketsFiltered
cdmipDroppedPacketsFiltered.description: The number of packets dropped because of a software decision.

cdmipDroppedPacketsMulticastDisableGroup.name: cdmipDroppedPacketsMulticastDisableGroup
cdmipDroppedPacketsMulticastDisableGroup.description: The number of multicast packets dropped because the IGMP multicast group is disabled.

cdmipDroppedPacketsNoArpEntry.name: cdmipDroppedPacketsNoArpEntry
cdmipDroppedPacketsNoArpEntry.description: The number of packets dropped because there is no ARP entry in the ARP table.

cdmipDroppedPacketsBadBufferLength.name: cdmipDroppedPacketsBadBufferLength
cdmipDroppedPacketsBadBufferLength.description: The number of packets dropped because of a bad buffer length.

cdmipDroppedPacketsBadIpVersion.name: cdmipDroppedPacketsBadIpVersion
cdmipDroppedPacketsBadIpVersion.description: The number of packets dropped because of an unsupported IP version (i.e. V6).

cdmipDroppedPacketsQosFilterRule.name: cdmipDroppedPacketsQosFilterRule
cdmipDroppedPacketsQosFilterRule.description: The number of packets filtered because of the 'Filter' flag on a QoS rule.

cdmipDroppedPacketsEasyConnectMulticastO.name: cdmipDroppedPacketsEasyConnectMulticastOption
cdmipDroppedPacketsEasyConnectMulticastO.description: The number of multicast packets dropped in EasyConnect mode because the Multicast Option is disabled.

cdmipDroppedPacketsRouterQueueFull.name: cdmipDroppedPacketsRouterQueueFull
cdmipDroppedPacketsRouterQueueFull.description: The total number of packets dropped because router queue is full.

cdmipResetCounters.name: cdmipResetCounters
cdmipResetCounters.description: Setting this parameter to '1' will clear all IP routing, WAN, and Ethernet statistics.

cdmipQosStatsQueueIndex.name: cdmipQosStatsQueueIndex
cdmipQosStatsQueueIndex.description: The index of the QoS rule for which stats are being displayed.

cdmipQosStatsSentPackets.name: cdmipQosStatsSentPackets
cdmipQosStatsSentPackets.description: The total number of packets sent through this QoS queue.

cdmipQosStatsSentPacketsPerSecond.name: cdmipQosStatsSentPacketsPerSecond
cdmipQosStatsSentPacketsPerSecond.description: The number of packets per second sent through this QoS queue.

cdmipQosStatsSentBytes.name: cdmipQosStatsSentBytes
cdmipQosStatsSentBytes.description: The total number of bytes sent through this QoS queue.

cdmipQosStatsDroppedPackets.name: cdmipQosStatsDroppedPackets
cdmipQosStatsDroppedPackets.description: The total number of packets dropped from this QoS queue.

cdmipQosStatsDroppedBytes.name: cdmipQosStatsDroppedBytes
cdmipQosStatsDroppedBytes.description: The total number of bytes dropped from this QoS queue.

cdmipQosStatsCurrentTxRate.name: cdmipQosStatsCurrentTxRate
cdmipQosStatsCurrentTxRate.description: The current Tx data rate associated with this QoS queue.

cdmipQosStatsAverageTxRate.name: cdmipQosStatsAverageTxRate
cdmipQosStatsAverageTxRate.description: The average Tx data rate associated with this QoS queue.

cdmipQosStatsMaxTxRate.name: cdmipQosStatsMaxTxRate
cdmipQosStatsMaxTxRate.description: The maximum Tx data rate associated with this QoS queue.

cdmipQosStatsActiveFlows.name: cdmipQosStatsActiveFlows
cdmipQosStatsActiveFlows.description: The number of active flows associated with this QoS queue.

cdmipQosStatsResetCounters.name: cdmipQosStatsResetCounters
cdmipQosStatsResetCounters.description: Setting this to '1' will reset all the statistics counters associated with this QoS queue.

cdmipWanFpgaRxBadAddrCount.name: cdmipWanFpgaRxBadAddrCount
cdmipWanFpgaRxBadAddrCount.description: The number of received frames from the Satellite interface that do not match any of the HDLC addresses or the broadcast address. If 'frame bypass' is enabled, then non-matching frames are not counted as having a bad address.

cdmipWanFpgaRxPktProcessorCrcErrorCount.name: cdmipWanFpgaRxPktProcessorCrcErrorCount
cdmipWanFpgaRxPktProcessorCrcErrorCount.description: The number of received frames from the Satellite interface that failed the packet processor CRC check.

cdmipWanFpgaRxAbortOctetErrorCount.name: cdmipWanFpgaRxAbortOctetErrorCount
cdmipWanFpgaRxAbortOctetErrorCount.description: The number of the aborted frames from the Satellite interface plus the number of octet error frames. An octet error is when the received frame does not start on a byte boudary.

cdmipWanFpgaRxOverrunErrorCount.name: cdmipWanFpgaRxOverrunErrorCount
cdmipWanFpgaRxOverrunErrorCount.description: The number of received frames from the Satellite interface that exceeded a max. frame length of 2K bytes in length or overflowed the HDLC buffer.

cdmipWanFpgaRxHdlcCrcErrorCount.name: cdmipWanFpgaRxHdlcCrcErrorCount
cdmipWanFpgaRxHdlcCrcErrorCount.description: The number of received frames from the Satellite interface that failed the HDLC CRC check.

cdmipWanFpgaRxHdlcPayLoadCount.name: cdmipWanFpgaRxHdlcPayLoadCount
cdmipWanFpgaRxHdlcPayLoadCount.description: The count of payload bytes that were received over the Satellite interface, excluding any frame overhead.

cdmipWanFpgaRxHdlcHeaderCount.name: cdmipWanFpgaRxHdlcHeaderCount
cdmipWanFpgaRxHdlcHeaderCount.description: The count of HDLC header bytes received over the Satellite interface, including control, HDLC address, Flow ID, and CRC.

cdmipWanFpgaRxHdlcPacketCount.name: cdmipWanFpgaRxHdlcPacketCount
cdmipWanFpgaRxHdlcPacketCount.description: The number of frames received over the Satellite interface.

cdmipWanFpgaTxHdlcHeaderCount.name: cdmipWanFpgaTxHdlcHeaderCount
cdmipWanFpgaTxHdlcHeaderCount.description: The number of HDLC header bytes transmitted over the Satellite interface.

cdmipWanFpgaTxHdlcPayLoadCount.name: cdmipWanFpgaTxHdlcPayLoadCount
cdmipWanFpgaTxHdlcPayLoadCount.description: The number of payload bytes transmitted over the Satellite interface.

cdmipWanFpgaTxHdlcPacketCount.name: cdmipWanFpgaTxHdlcPacketCount
cdmipWanFpgaTxHdlcPacketCount.description: The number of packets transmitted over the Satellite interface.

cdmipWanFpgaResetAllCounters.name: cdmipWanFpgaResetAllCounters
cdmipWanFpgaResetAllCounters.description: Setting this variable to 'reset' will reset all the WAN FPGA Rx & Tx counters.

cdmipWanFpgaWanUtilization.name: cdmipWanFpgaWanUtilization
cdmipWanFpgaWanUtilization.description: The percentage (%) of Tx bandwidth that is being utilized.

cdmipWanFpgaLanToWanTraffic.name: cdmipWanFpgaLanToWanTraffic
cdmipWanFpgaLanToWanTraffic.description: The data rate (Kbps) before IP header and payload compression of Ethernet traffic destined for the Satellite interface.

cdmipWanFpgaActualWanTraffic.name: cdmipWanFpgaActualWanTraffic
cdmipWanFpgaActualWanTraffic.description: The 'compressed' data rate (Kbps) after IP header and payload compression of traffic transmitted on the Satellite interface.

cdmipWanFpgaWanBandwidthSaved.name: cdmipWanFpgaWanBandwidthSaved
cdmipWanFpgaWanBandwidthSaved.description: The percentage (%) of Satellite bandwidth saved because of IP header and payload compression.

cdmipHdrcompStatsQueueIndex.name: cdmipHdrcompStatsQueueIndex
cdmipHdrcompStatsQueueIndex.description: The index of the QoS queue for which the IP header compression stats are being displayed.

cdmipHdrcompStatsPreHdrcompBytes.name: cdmipHdrcompStatsPreHdrcompBytes
cdmipHdrcompStatsPreHdrcompBytes.description: The total number of bytes in all packets before IP header compression has been performed.

cdmipHdrcompStatsPostHdrcompBytes.name: cdmipHdrcompStatsPostHdrcompBytes
cdmipHdrcompStatsPostHdrcompBytes.description: The total number of bytes in all 'compressed' packets after IP header compression has been performed.

cdmipHdrcompRatio.name: cdmipHdrcompRatio
cdmipHdrcompRatio.description: The percentage (%) of saving gained by performing IP header compression on all packets destined for the Satellite interface. The percentage is then multiplied by 100 to make it an integer.

cdmipPayloadCompPrePayloadCompBytes.name: cdmipPayloadCompPrePayloadCompBytes
cdmipPayloadCompPrePayloadCompBytes.description: The total number of bytes in all packets before payload compression has been performed. To get the standard payload compression ratio in the form 1:x.xx (Pre Payload Compression Bytes) x.xx = ------------------------------- (Post Payload Compression Bytes)

cdmipPayloadCompPostPayloadCompBytes.name: cdmipPayloadCompPostPayloadCompBytes
cdmipPayloadCompPostPayloadCompBytes.description: The total number of bytes in all packets after payload compression has been performed. To get the standard payload compression ratio in the form 1:x.xx (Pre Payload Compression Bytes) x.xx = ------------------------------- (Post Payload Compression Bytes)

cdmipPayloadCompRatio.name: cdmipPayloadCompRatio
cdmipPayloadCompRatio.description: This parameter is the standard payload compression ratio. To get the standard payload compression ratio in the form 1:x.xx (Pre Payload Compression Bytes) x.xx = ------------------------------- (Post Payload Compression Bytes) The ratio is then converted into an integer by multiplying by 100.

cdmipCompStatsResetCounters.name: cdmipCompStatsResetCounters
cdmipCompStatsResetCounters.description: Setting this to '1' will reset all IP header compression and payload compression stats counters.

cdmipQosRulesIndex.name: cdmipQosRulesIndex
cdmipQosRulesIndex.description: The index for the QoS rule. The valid values are 1 - 32.

cdmipQosRulesSrcIpAddr.name: cdmipQosRulesSrcIpAddr
cdmipQosRulesSrcIpAddr.description: The source IP address for the QoS rule.

cdmipQosRulesSrcIpMaskLen.name: cdmipQosRulesSrcIpMaskLen
cdmipQosRulesSrcIpMaskLen.description: The source IP subnet mask length for the QoS rule.

cdmipQosRulesDstIpAddr.name: cdmipQosRulesDstIpAddr
cdmipQosRulesDstIpAddr.description: The destination IP address for the QoS rule.

cdmipQosRulesDstIpMaskLen.name: cdmipQosRulesDstIpMaskLen
cdmipQosRulesDstIpMaskLen.description: The destination IP subnet mask length for the QoS rule.

cdmipQosRulesProtocol.name: cdmipQosRulesProtocol
cdmipQosRulesProtocol.description: The protocol type for the QoS rule. Only the default rule is configured with 'All'. Setting protocol field to 'All' for other rules is not permitted, may result in 'wrong value' Setting the protocol to Non-IP would configure the QoS rule parameters to pre-set default values. User is only allowed to set max bandwidth, priority & filter flag for a Non-IP qos rule. User is not allowed to create/modify a rule with RTP Signaling protocol. The software does this. IMPORTANT: Configure rtpSignal rule for rtpVoice/rtpVideo rules.

cdmipQosRulesSrcPortMin.name: cdmipQosRulesSrcPortMin
cdmipQosRulesSrcPortMin.description: The starting UDP/TCP source port (minimum) for the QoS rule. A QoS rule can be configured with a port range of aaaa - bbbb by setting 'cdmipQosRulesSrcPortMin' to aaaa and 'cdmipQosRulesSrcPortMax' to bbbb. *** NOTE: Enter 65536 to match all ports. ***

cdmipQosRulesSrcPortMax.name: cdmipQosRulesSrcPortMax
cdmipQosRulesSrcPortMax.description: The ending UDP/TCP source port (maximum) for the QoS rule. A QoS rule can be configured with a port range of aaaa - bbbb by setting 'cdmipQosRulesSrcPortMin' to aaaa and 'cdmipQosRulesSrcPortMax' to bbbb. *** NOTE: Enter 65536 to match all ports. ***

cdmipQosRulesDstPortMin.name: cdmipQosRulesDstPortMin
cdmipQosRulesDstPortMin.description: The starting destination port number (minimum) for the QoS rule. A QoS rule can be configured with a port range of xxxx - yyyy by setting 'cdmipQosRulesDstPortMin' to xxxx and 'cdmipQosRulesDstPortMax' to yyyy. *** NOTE: Enter 65536 for match all ports. ***

cdmipQosRulesDstPortMax.name: cdmipQosRulesDstPortMax
cdmipQosRulesDstPortMax.description: The ending destination port number (maximum) for the QoS rule. A QoS rule can be configured with a port range of xxxx - yyyy by setting 'cdmipQosRulesDstPortMin' to xxxx and 'cdmipQosRulesDstPortMax' to yyyy. *** NOTE: Enter 65536 for match all ports. ***

cdmipQosRulesMinBw.name: cdmipQosRulesMinBw
cdmipQosRulesMinBw.description: The minimum bandwidth (Kbps) for the QoS rule. *** NOTE: Only valid for 'Minimum Bandwidth & Maximum Bandwidth' mode. ***

cdmipQosRulesMaxBw.name: cdmipQosRulesMaxBw
cdmipQosRulesMaxBw.description: The maximum bandwidth (Kbps) for the QoS rule. *** NOTE: Valid for both 'Maximum Bandwidth & Priority' and 'Minimum Bandwidth & Maximum Bandwidth' modes. ***

cdmipQosRulesPriority.name: cdmipQosRulesPriority
cdmipQosRulesPriority.description: The priority for the QoS rule. The valid values are: Priority 1 - Highest Priority 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7 - Middle Priority 8 - Lowest *** NOTE: Only valid for 'Maximum Bandwidth & Priority' mode. ***

cdmipQosRulesWred.name: cdmipQosRulesWred
cdmipQosRulesWred.description: The WRED (Weighted Random Early Drop) option for the QoS rule. This is the mechanism by which packets are treated upon queue full. If this is enabled, the packets are dropped randomly upon detection of queue full or queue getting full.

cdmipQosRulesFilter.name: cdmipQosRulesFilter
cdmipQosRulesFilter.description: The filter option for the QoS rule. *** NOTE: This option will filter ALL packets associated with this QoS rule. ***

cdmipQosRulesRowStatus.name: cdmipQosRulesRowStatus
cdmipQosRulesRowStatus.description: In SMIv2 tables, the RowStatus textual convention is used to manage the creation and deletion of conceptual rows. This column has six defined values. active(1) - which indicates that the conceptual row with all column is available for use by the managed device. notInService(2) - this row state is not yet supported. notReady(3) - this row state is not yet supported. createAndGo(4) - which is supplied by a manager wishing to create a new instance of a conceptual row and to have its status automatically set to active, making it available for use by the managed device. createAndWait(5) - this row create is not yet supported destroy(6) - which is supplied by a manager wishing to delete all of the instances associated with an existing conceptual row.

cdmipDiffServRulesIndex.name: cdmipDiffServRulesIndex
cdmipDiffServRulesIndex.description: The index for the DiffServ rule.

cdmipDiffServRulesClass.name: cdmipDiffServRulesClass
cdmipDiffServRulesClass.description: The DiffServ class name for the DiffServ rule. There are three types of DiffServ rules: 1. Expedite Forwarding 2. Class-1 to Class-8 3. Assured Forwarding-1 to Assured Forwarding-4 *** NOTE: This is NOT a user configurable parameter. ***

cdmipDiffServRulesDscp.name: cdmipDiffServRulesDscp
cdmipDiffServRulesDscp.description: The DiffServ code point (DSCP) for the DiffServ rule. *** NOTE: This is NOT a user configurable parameter. ***

cdmipDiffServRulesMinBw.name: cdmipDiffServRulesMinBw
cdmipDiffServRulesMinBw.description: The minimum bandwidth (Kbps) for the DiffServ rule. *** NOTE: This value can only be set for DiffServ rules of 'Assured Forwarding Class'. NOTE: The total minimum bandwidth of all rules should NOT exceed the Tx data rate of the modem. ***

cdmipDiffServRulesMaxBw.name: cdmipDiffServRulesMaxBw
cdmipDiffServRulesMaxBw.description: The maximum bandwidth (Kbps) for the DiffServ rule. *** NOTE: This value can only be set for DiffServ rules of 'Assured Forwarding Class'. ***

cdmipDiffServRulesPriority.name: cdmipDiffServRulesPriority
cdmipDiffServRulesPriority.description: The priority of the DiffServ rule. *** NOTE: This is NOT a user configurable parameter. ***

cdmipDiffServRulesRowStatus.name: cdmipDiffServRulesRowStatus
cdmipDiffServRulesRowStatus.description: In SMIv2 tables, the RowStatus textual convention is used to manage the creation and deletion of conceptual rows. This column has six defined values. active(1) - which indicates that the conceptual row with all column is available for use by the managed device notInService(2) - this row state is not yet supported notReady(3) - this row state is not yet supported createAndGo(4) - which is supplied by a manager wishing to create a new instance of a conceptual row and to have its status automatically set to active, making it available for use by the managed device. createAndWait(5) - this row create is not yet supported destroy(6) - which is supplied by a manager wishing to delete all of the instances associated with an existing conceptual row. Right now, the diffserv initialisation process creates all necessary Diffserv rules. User is allowed to modify minBw & maxBw for ASF (Assured Forwarding) class rules only. User is not allowed to create new rules.

cdmipQosMode.name: cdmipQosMode
cdmipQosMode.description: The QoS configuration modes for the QoS subsystem. The valid values are: 1. Maximum Bandwidth & Priority. 2. Minimum Bandwidth & Maximum Bandwidth. 3. Differential Services Mode.
